1
00:00:10,967 --> 00:00:12,300
<i> What if your mom's right?</i>

2
00:00:12,433 --> 00:00:15,467
<i>This engagement
feels kind of fast.</i>

3
00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:16,733
<i> So you've made your decision.</i>

4
00:00:16,867 --> 00:00:18,033
<i> Edward, I'm sorry.</i>

5
00:00:18,167 --> 00:00:21,733
<i>Can't you see this woman
is tearing our family apart?</i>

6
00:00:21,867 --> 00:00:24,433
<i>And there's nothing you
or Edward can do to stop it!</i>

7
00:00:24,567 --> 00:00:25,567
<i>If you go through
with this marriage,</i>

8
00:00:25,700 --> 00:00:26,967
<i> you're going to be miserable.</i>

9
00:00:27,100 --> 00:00:29,367
<i>What he said won't happen,
right?</i>

10
00:00:29,500 --> 00:00:31,167
<i> Of course not.</i>

11
00:00:31,300 --> 00:00:32,600
<i> So, how's Paolo anyway?</i>

12
00:00:32,733 --> 00:00:34,467
<i>He's the worst person
you could choose over me.</i>

13
00:00:34,633 --> 00:00:37,233
<i>He's a traitor. He steals
what isn't his. He's selfish.</i>

14
00:00:37,367 --> 00:00:38,600
<i> You ruined the relationship</i>

15
00:00:38,733 --> 00:00:40,867
<i>we spent years building
with Mr. Chen!</i>

16
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:43,133
<i> You're fired! Get out!</i>

17
00:00:43,267 --> 00:00:44,533
<i> Get out of our house, too!</i>

18
00:00:44,667 --> 00:00:47,433
<i>I don't want to see your face
when I come home.</i>

19
00:00:47,567 --> 00:00:50,267
<i>You know, I can't even blame you
for not liking me.</i>

20
00:00:50,400 --> 00:00:51,767
<i>My own father
doesn't even want me.</i>

21
00:00:51,900 --> 00:00:54,267
<i>I'm sure your father was just
shocked. That's why he said it.</i>

22
00:00:54,400 --> 00:00:56,967
<i>He was very clear.
He wants me out of this house.</i>

23
00:00:57,100 --> 00:00:58,967
<i>This is all
Marj Castillo's fault.</i>

24
00:00:59,100 --> 00:01:01,300
<i>She's the one destroying
our family.</i>

25
00:01:04,700 --> 00:01:06,967
<i> We're sorry, the number...</i>

26
00:01:14,700 --> 00:01:17,367
<i> We're sorry, the number...</i>

27
00:01:21,467 --> 00:01:22,800
That was Edward, right?

28
00:01:24,567 --> 00:01:26,333
Just leave him alone for now.

29
00:01:26,467 --> 00:01:27,800
He needs time to heal.

30
00:01:29,167 --> 00:01:31,733
Did you hear what happened?

31
00:01:31,867 --> 00:01:33,600
It was just this morning.

32
00:01:33,733 --> 00:01:36,067
I only found out...

33
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:38,667
when Mr. Chen complained to dad.

34
00:01:40,033 --> 00:01:42,133
Hon, Edward needs time to heal.

35
00:01:42,300 --> 00:01:43,667
Eventually,

36
00:01:43,800 --> 00:01:45,100
he'll accept us.

37
00:01:47,033 --> 00:01:48,333
I hope so.

38
00:01:51,433 --> 00:01:55,467
I hope things cool down
between him and your dad, too.

39
00:01:55,600 --> 00:01:56,867
Hey.

40
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:58,400
You're doing it again.

41
00:01:59,767 --> 00:02:01,367
Doing what?

42
00:02:01,500 --> 00:02:06,633
Worrying too much about people
you don't need to worry about.

43
00:02:06,767 --> 00:02:10,100
Can you stop carrying
other people's problems?

44
00:02:10,233 --> 00:02:13,367
Can you blame me?
Edward's my friend.

45
00:02:15,267 --> 00:02:17,000
Okay, how about this?

46
00:02:17,133 --> 00:02:19,433
Let me take this burden.

47
00:02:19,567 --> 00:02:22,200
I'll talk to Edward.

48
00:02:22,333 --> 00:02:25,900
I'll tell you
whatever comes out of it.

49
00:02:27,300 --> 00:02:28,267
Okay?

50
00:02:29,867 --> 00:02:30,833
Okay.

51
00:02:32,167 --> 00:02:33,233
For now, let's focus

52
00:02:33,367 --> 00:02:36,667
on our engagement party
and wedding preparations.

53
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:37,967
Is that okay?

54
00:02:39,333 --> 00:02:40,633
I love you.

55
00:02:48,967 --> 00:02:50,333
Are you okay now?

56
00:03:53,500 --> 00:03:57,233
Ma'am Regina, you called for me?

57
00:03:57,400 --> 00:03:58,600
Sit down.

58
00:04:14,833 --> 00:04:17,433
You know what you did,
don't you?

59
00:04:19,833 --> 00:04:21,233
Ma'am?

60
00:04:21,367 --> 00:04:24,267
Come on. Stop pretending.

61
00:04:24,400 --> 00:04:26,533
You know you destroyed
my family

62
00:04:26,667 --> 00:04:29,633
because you want the name and
the prestige that comes with it.

63
00:04:32,700 --> 00:04:36,067
I never intended
for that to happen.

64
00:04:36,200 --> 00:04:39,233
So you admit it's your fault.

65
00:04:40,267 --> 00:04:41,600
I'm sorry.

66
00:04:42,633 --> 00:04:44,533
I never wanted things
to go this far.

67
00:04:44,667 --> 00:04:47,500
Then you shouldn't have agreed
to marry Paolo.

68
00:04:47,633 --> 00:04:49,767
You knew the brothers
were fighting because of you,

69
00:04:49,900 --> 00:04:52,133
and you made it worse
with your ambition!

70
00:04:53,533 --> 00:04:54,533
Regina!

71
00:04:56,267 --> 00:04:57,933
Don't scold Marj.

72
00:04:58,067 --> 00:05:00,033
Don't blame her.

73
00:05:00,167 --> 00:05:06,033
I decided to kick Edward out
solely because he's a disgrace!

74
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:10,067
I should've taught that boy
a lesson a long time ago.

75
00:05:11,233 --> 00:05:15,200
All he ever does is mess up
and embarrass this family.

76
00:05:16,667 --> 00:05:18,567
If anyone's at fault here,

77
00:05:18,700 --> 00:05:20,367
it's you, Regina.

78
00:05:20,500 --> 00:05:22,800
You raised Edward
to be a spoiled brat.

79
00:05:31,433 --> 00:05:32,567
Excuse me.

80
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:47,567
Congratulations.

81
00:05:48,733 --> 00:05:49,500
Thank you.

82
00:05:49,633 --> 00:05:51,767
Marj's here. Good evening.

83
00:05:51,900 --> 00:05:52,833
- Thank you.
- Congrats, Sir.

84
00:05:52,967 --> 00:05:54,100
Thank you.

85
00:05:54,233 --> 00:05:55,900
- Good evening.
- Marj, congratulations.

86
00:05:56,033 --> 00:05:57,100
- Thanks for coming.
- Thank you.

87
00:05:57,233 --> 00:05:58,900
Thank you.

88
00:05:59,033 --> 00:06:00,600
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

89
00:06:03,800 --> 00:06:05,467
- Marj, congratulations.
- Thank you.

90
00:06:05,600 --> 00:06:08,367
- Thank you for coming.
- Thank you.

91
00:06:08,533 --> 00:06:09,467
Enjoy.

92
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:12,233
Let me fix your hair, Love.

93
00:06:13,600 --> 00:06:14,933
You're so sweet.

94
00:06:16,333 --> 00:06:18,567
You look so handsome.

95
00:06:18,700 --> 00:06:20,167
You're more beautiful.

96
00:06:31,200 --> 00:06:32,333
It feels like...

97
00:06:33,367 --> 00:06:37,267
your mom's glare is stabbing me.

98
00:06:45,167 --> 00:06:46,800
Just ignore her.

99
00:06:46,933 --> 00:06:48,267
She'll get over it.

100
00:06:50,100 --> 00:06:51,467
What if she doesn't?

101
00:06:53,333 --> 00:06:55,933
Then it stops...

102
00:06:56,067 --> 00:06:58,100
being our business.

103
00:06:58,233 --> 00:06:59,167
Okay?

104
00:06:59,300 --> 00:07:01,733
She's the one
creating the headache, anyway.

105
00:07:01,867 --> 00:07:03,967
She's just looking
for someone to blame

106
00:07:04,100 --> 00:07:06,633
for losing her favorite child.

107
00:07:06,767 --> 00:07:08,567
Honestly,

108
00:07:08,700 --> 00:07:09,967
she's been looking at me
like that, too.

109
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:14,000
Don't worry.

110
00:07:14,167 --> 00:07:16,333
She'll come around. Promise.

111
00:07:16,467 --> 00:07:17,800
She's actually kind.

112
00:07:19,333 --> 00:07:21,933
Just relax and enjoy the party,
okay?

113
00:07:22,067 --> 00:07:23,133
Okay.

114
00:07:29,400 --> 00:07:31,300
<i>- Sir Paolo, congrats.
- Thank you.</i>

115
00:07:31,433 --> 00:07:33,233
Thank you.

116
00:07:34,267 --> 00:07:36,367
- Thank you, thank you.
- Thank you.

117
00:07:36,500 --> 00:07:37,733
Come in.

118
00:07:44,667 --> 00:07:45,867
There they are, Mom.

119
00:07:47,500 --> 00:07:48,167
Enjoy the night.

120
00:07:48,300 --> 00:07:50,333
Yes, that's them.

121
00:07:55,667 --> 00:07:58,533
Excuse me, Ma'am, Sir.

122
00:07:58,667 --> 00:08:03,633
Let me introduce my mom
and my brother, Jobert.

123
00:08:03,767 --> 00:08:06,200
Hello. I'm Evelyn.

124
00:08:06,333 --> 00:08:07,800
Just call me Greg.

125
00:08:07,933 --> 00:08:10,133
And this is my wife, Regina.

126
00:08:10,267 --> 00:08:12,633
Thank you for the invitation.

127
00:08:12,767 --> 00:08:13,633
Hello.

128
00:08:13,767 --> 00:08:15,567
I hope this marks the beginning

129
00:08:15,700 --> 00:08:19,067
of a good relationship
between our families.

130
00:08:20,100 --> 00:08:21,600
Of course.

131
00:08:24,833 --> 00:08:26,667
Now I know...

132
00:08:26,800 --> 00:08:28,567
where your beauty comes from,
Marj.

133
00:08:30,667 --> 00:08:33,167
No, no. No.

134
00:08:33,300 --> 00:08:34,900
<i> This is embarassing.</i>

135
00:08:35,033 --> 00:08:38,533
Sir, my mom's way prettier
than me.

136
00:08:38,667 --> 00:08:40,867
Marj, please.

137
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:42,333
Call me dad.

138
00:08:42,467 --> 00:08:43,833
And call Regina mom.

139
00:08:44,967 --> 00:08:46,933
Yes, yes. Yes, of course.

140
00:08:50,533 --> 00:08:54,900
<i>And of course, let's call
our newly engaged couple,</i>

141
00:08:55,067 --> 00:08:56,367
<i> Paolo and Marj!</i>

142
00:09:18,367 --> 00:09:21,100
I'm raising my glass
to my son, Paolo,

143
00:09:22,767 --> 00:09:27,667
and to his beautiful and kind
bride-to-be.

144
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:30,100
And to the future
they'll face together.

145
00:09:31,667 --> 00:09:33,033
It won't be easy.

146
00:09:34,067 --> 00:09:35,767
<i> It won't always be nice.</i>

147
00:09:36,867 --> 00:09:39,700
But because of your love
for one another,

148
00:09:39,833 --> 00:09:41,700
you'll overcome everything.

149
00:09:43,567 --> 00:09:48,467
You may not have known
each other long,

150
00:09:49,867 --> 00:09:57,067
but you can look to Regina
and me as an example.

151
00:09:57,200 --> 00:10:00,900
We're still standing strong,

152
00:10:02,900 --> 00:10:07,900
even though we also got married
right away.

153
00:10:15,067 --> 00:10:18,867
Here's to a lifetime of getting
to know each other.

154
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:21,600
I'm looking forward
to your life together.

155
00:10:21,733 --> 00:10:23,500
Paolo, Marj, cheers!

156
00:10:23,633 --> 00:10:26,633
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

157
00:10:31,767 --> 00:10:32,600
<i> So, Miss Regina,</i>

158
00:10:32,733 --> 00:10:33,900
how does it feel

159
00:10:34,033 --> 00:10:37,233
knowing Marj will be
your future daughter-in-law?

160
00:10:39,233 --> 00:10:42,600
Oh my gosh,
I'm more than thrilled.

161
00:10:42,733 --> 00:10:45,333
I'm so excited to welcome you

162
00:10:45,467 --> 00:10:48,233
into the Torrecampo family,
Marj.

163
00:10:49,367 --> 00:10:51,500
<i> Ma'am, Sir, photo please.</i>

164
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:53,633
Please.

165
00:10:54,800 --> 00:10:57,633
Evelyn, Jobert, come join us.

166
00:10:58,900 --> 00:11:00,067
<i> Jobert!</i>

167
00:11:02,233 --> 00:11:04,600
Because you hurt my family,

168
00:11:05,667 --> 00:11:11,833
I will never accept you,
even if you marry Paolo.

169
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:17,767
Get ready to be miserable
in my house, Marj.

170
00:11:19,933 --> 00:11:22,167
Come on, let's take the photo.

171
00:11:22,300 --> 00:11:23,800
Okay, okay.

172
00:12:12,667 --> 00:12:14,033
Sorry, sorry.

173
00:12:16,333 --> 00:12:17,633
Are you okay?

174
00:12:31,667 --> 00:12:33,000
Everything all right, Love?

175
00:12:34,767 --> 00:12:37,467
I'm just not used to this yet.

176
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:40,633
I'm not really used
to fancy stuff like this.

177
00:12:40,767 --> 00:12:43,000
Well, you'd better
get used to it.

178
00:12:43,133 --> 00:12:45,700
Especially once we're married.

179
00:12:45,833 --> 00:12:46,800
I know.

180
00:12:47,967 --> 00:12:49,233
I should be happy.

181
00:12:49,367 --> 00:12:52,667
A lot of good things
are happening to me right now.

182
00:12:52,800 --> 00:12:54,733
But...

183
00:12:54,867 --> 00:12:56,500
I don't know...

184
00:12:56,633 --> 00:12:59,267
I can't help feeling
like something bad is coming.

185
00:13:00,733 --> 00:13:03,000
That's always how
it goes for me.

186
00:13:03,133 --> 00:13:04,433
I get it.

187
00:13:04,567 --> 00:13:07,400
Like every time
something good happens,

188
00:13:07,533 --> 00:13:11,267
something bad has to follow.

189
00:13:11,400 --> 00:13:15,000
Something that completely
cancels out the happiness.

190
00:13:15,133 --> 00:13:17,867
Do you feel that, too?

191
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:19,267
Not really.

192
00:13:19,400 --> 00:13:23,333
But Edward,
that's how he always thinks.

193
00:13:23,500 --> 00:13:26,400
Like I always tell my brother,
okay?

194
00:13:26,533 --> 00:13:29,600
We're responsible
for our own actions.

195
00:13:29,733 --> 00:13:33,967
And it's our choice
whether we stay happy or not.

196
00:13:36,633 --> 00:13:38,800
<i> Yeah, yeah, that's me.</i>

197
00:13:38,933 --> 00:13:43,633
I closed the FSPD accounts,
the Gochingte accounts.

198
00:13:43,767 --> 00:13:47,533
And just recently,
I brought in Sutherland Homes.

199
00:13:47,667 --> 00:13:49,500
Wow.

200
00:13:49,633 --> 00:13:52,400
Your clients must
really trust you.

201
00:13:53,500 --> 00:13:55,000
Well...

202
00:13:55,167 --> 00:13:57,000
they should.

203
00:13:57,133 --> 00:14:00,833
Honestly,
between my brother and me,

204
00:14:00,967 --> 00:14:03,200
I'm the better one.

205
00:14:03,333 --> 00:14:04,833
I'm smarter.

206
00:14:04,967 --> 00:14:07,200
I'm more passionate
about the job.

207
00:14:07,333 --> 00:14:09,633
My brother?

208
00:14:09,767 --> 00:14:12,500
All he does is party.

209
00:14:14,333 --> 00:14:16,167
Like the one they're having now?

210
00:14:17,233 --> 00:14:19,100
Why aren't you there?

211
00:14:21,400 --> 00:14:24,000
I wouldn't enjoy it.

212
00:14:24,133 --> 00:14:26,333
I'd just run into people
I don't want to see.

213
00:14:33,700 --> 00:14:34,867
Wait.

214
00:14:41,367 --> 00:14:44,100
Marj Castillo is marrying
your brother?

215
00:14:45,467 --> 00:14:47,500
Yeah. Why?

216
00:14:47,633 --> 00:14:49,000
Do you know her?

217
00:14:51,733 --> 00:14:53,767
Of course.

218
00:14:53,900 --> 00:14:55,767
We used to work
together in Batangas.

219
00:15:01,367 --> 00:15:05,533
So Marj's becoming
a Torrecampo now?

220
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:16,933
Don't worry, okay?

221
00:15:17,067 --> 00:15:18,967
You'll be a Torrecampo soon.

222
00:15:20,033 --> 00:15:23,567
A lot of women would kill
for that opportunity.

223
00:15:27,933 --> 00:15:30,100
But, Love...

224
00:15:30,233 --> 00:15:35,733
our engagement hurts
Edward and your mom.

225
00:15:37,233 --> 00:15:40,833
And I don't like it
when I'm hurting people.

226
00:15:41,867 --> 00:15:44,867
I know that
no matter what we do,

227
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:47,167
they'll never accept
our relationship.

228
00:15:49,833 --> 00:15:51,200
So what are you saying, Love?

229
00:15:58,000 --> 00:16:00,833
Maybe we shouldn't go through
with this.

230
00:16:00,967 --> 00:16:03,333
Maybe getting married
isn't the right thing.

231
00:16:08,833 --> 00:16:09,933
Love,

232
00:16:11,533 --> 00:16:13,633
don't think like that.

233
00:16:13,767 --> 00:16:16,633
It doesn't matter
what they think.

234
00:16:16,767 --> 00:16:19,567
What matters is that
we love each other.

235
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:22,733
And...

236
00:16:22,867 --> 00:16:24,500
I'll talk to mom.

237
00:16:24,633 --> 00:16:27,233
I'll ask her to help you
with the wedding preparations,

238
00:16:27,367 --> 00:16:31,333
so you two can bond,
and she can warm up to you.

239
00:16:31,467 --> 00:16:34,000
And Edward...

240
00:16:34,133 --> 00:16:36,000
He'll eventually move on
from you.

241
00:16:36,133 --> 00:16:38,933
Especially once he meets
someone else.

242
00:16:39,067 --> 00:16:40,367
Okay?

243
00:16:52,467 --> 00:16:54,733
<i>Sorry, I've been yapping
all night.</i>

244
00:16:54,867 --> 00:16:58,900
No, no.
I actually like talks like this.

245
00:16:59,033 --> 00:17:03,200
Besides, it makes me
even more interested in you.

246
00:17:04,967 --> 00:17:08,467
I'm lucky you're single, Edward.

247
00:17:08,600 --> 00:17:10,967
Forget about your brother
and Marj.

248
00:17:12,433 --> 00:17:13,833
You have me.

249
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:17,100
It's really nice
talking to you...

250
00:17:17,233 --> 00:17:18,833
Thea.

251
00:17:27,733 --> 00:17:29,567
I still can't believe

252
00:17:29,700 --> 00:17:34,033
I'm having drinks with one
of the Torrecampo sons.

253
00:17:34,167 --> 00:17:38,167
Wow. You know, I've always
really admired your family.

254
00:17:38,300 --> 00:17:41,833
Trust me, there's nothing
special about us.

255
00:17:41,967 --> 00:17:42,767
If you only knew,

256
00:17:42,900 --> 00:17:45,933
being a Torrecampo
comes with pressure.

257
00:17:46,067 --> 00:17:48,267
High expectations.

258
00:17:48,433 --> 00:17:50,767
That name carries
a lot of weight.

259
00:17:50,900 --> 00:17:52,133
Wow,

260
00:17:52,267 --> 00:17:54,467
you're being super humble.

261
00:17:54,600 --> 00:17:58,233
But honestly,
I get that pressure.

262
00:17:58,367 --> 00:18:00,767
I feel the same way,
as a Villareal.

263
00:18:00,900 --> 00:18:04,900
It's like
you always have to be perfect.

264
00:18:05,033 --> 00:18:06,333
Polished.

265
00:18:06,467 --> 00:18:09,167
Always meeting expectations.

266
00:18:11,400 --> 00:18:13,133
We're actually the same.

267
00:18:13,267 --> 00:18:15,367
Sometimes I even think
our family names

268
00:18:15,500 --> 00:18:17,867
are more of a curse.

269
00:18:20,100 --> 00:18:21,767
Amen to that.

270
00:18:21,933 --> 00:18:23,233
Cheers!

271
00:18:27,133 --> 00:18:30,333
We really have a lot in common.

272
00:18:31,500 --> 00:18:34,600
No wonder we click so easily.

273
00:18:37,333 --> 00:18:38,333
I agree.

274
00:18:39,533 --> 00:18:41,833
I really enjoyed
our conversation.

275
00:18:45,400 --> 00:18:48,200
Do you want...

276
00:18:48,333 --> 00:18:53,767
to continue this
somewhere quieter?

277
00:18:58,833 --> 00:19:00,700
Perhaps...

278
00:19:00,833 --> 00:19:02,233
at your place?

279
00:19:06,367 --> 00:19:07,167
Come on, Marj.

280
00:19:07,300 --> 00:19:09,133
Let me show you
a little preview.

281
00:19:14,733 --> 00:19:16,633
This wing of the house...

282
00:19:16,767 --> 00:19:19,400
will be yours and Paolo's
once you're married.

283
00:19:19,533 --> 00:19:21,767
I already had the rooms fixed.

284
00:19:21,900 --> 00:19:23,867
Repainted them, too.

285
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:25,433
Warm but classic.

286
00:19:26,867 --> 00:19:28,133
Really?

287
00:19:28,300 --> 00:19:29,600
Yes, Love.

288
00:19:29,733 --> 00:19:32,567
He also made sure
Jobert's room is closer,

289
00:19:32,700 --> 00:19:34,033
so you can check on him anytime.

290
00:19:35,467 --> 00:19:38,033
I also assigned Yolly
to take care of Jobert

291
00:19:38,167 --> 00:19:40,267
whenever you and Paolo
are at work.

292
00:19:40,400 --> 00:19:43,233
Ma'am, I've taken care
of Sir Edward and Sir Paolo

293
00:19:43,367 --> 00:19:45,267
since they were kids.

294
00:19:45,400 --> 00:19:47,767
I'm really happy.

295
00:19:47,900 --> 00:19:51,300
There's a new kid I have
to take care of. Jobert.

296
00:19:51,433 --> 00:19:54,667
And we're all excited
for you to move into the house.

297
00:19:54,800 --> 00:19:58,500
My brother will be so happy
when he hears about this.

298
00:19:58,633 --> 00:20:01,467
Thank you so much, Sir.

299
00:20:01,600 --> 00:20:03,533
All right, Ma'am.
I'll be in the kitchen.

300
00:20:07,400 --> 00:20:08,367
Marj...

301
00:20:08,500 --> 00:20:10,667
Paolo mentioned
that you and Regina

302
00:20:10,800 --> 00:20:13,333
aren't very comfortable
with each other yet.

303
00:20:15,100 --> 00:20:17,233
I don't think
you should worry about it.

304
00:20:17,367 --> 00:20:21,467
I was wary of you at first,
too, remember?

305
00:20:21,600 --> 00:20:24,733
But eventually, we got along.

306
00:20:24,867 --> 00:20:26,100
So just relax.

307
00:20:26,233 --> 00:20:28,133
You'll win Regina over.

308
00:20:29,967 --> 00:20:34,433
Yeah, mom does seem
to keep testing Marj.

309
00:20:36,767 --> 00:20:38,500
Marj...

310
00:20:38,633 --> 00:20:42,433
Regina can be intense,

311
00:20:42,567 --> 00:20:48,333
but she just wants to make sure
Paolo will be happy.

312
00:20:48,467 --> 00:20:52,600
Once she sees
how grounded you are,

313
00:20:52,733 --> 00:20:54,100
she'll come around.

314
00:20:55,100 --> 00:20:56,600
And besides,

315
00:20:56,733 --> 00:20:59,833
I still run this house.

316
00:20:59,967 --> 00:21:01,167
Right?

317
00:21:01,300 --> 00:21:02,467
Yes, Dad.

318
00:21:02,600 --> 00:21:05,200
So my wife doesn't really
have a choice.

319
00:21:05,333 --> 00:21:09,733
Thank you for making me
feel welcome in your home.

320
00:21:09,900 --> 00:21:12,133
Our home.

321
00:21:12,267 --> 00:21:13,633
Welcome home, Marj.

322
00:21:30,533 --> 00:21:33,067
<i> Don't worry. I'm here.</i>

323
00:21:33,200 --> 00:21:34,600
<i> We're partners, right?</i>

324
00:21:34,733 --> 00:21:37,333
<i>I've got you
when things get tough.</i>

325
00:21:37,467 --> 00:21:38,867
<i> Thank you, Marj.</i>

326
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:40,367
<i> I'll remember that.</i>

327
00:21:41,800 --> 00:21:43,567
Wait. Wait, wait.

328
00:21:45,833 --> 00:21:47,767
- Sorry.
- Why?

329
00:21:47,900 --> 00:21:50,067
Too fast?

330
00:21:50,200 --> 00:21:52,000
You're the one
who brought me here.

331
00:21:53,233 --> 00:21:55,000
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

332
00:21:55,133 --> 00:21:56,467
This is embarrassing.

333
00:21:57,500 --> 00:21:59,400
It's okay.

334
00:21:59,533 --> 00:22:01,833
There are no rules tonight.

335
00:22:04,767 --> 00:22:06,467
I thought I could.

336
00:22:06,600 --> 00:22:08,000
But I guess I can't.

337
00:22:09,900 --> 00:22:11,233
Let me guess.

338
00:22:12,800 --> 00:22:15,500
You're not over
someone yet, right?

339
00:22:22,967 --> 00:22:23,933
Thea...

340
00:22:25,167 --> 00:22:26,967
I just don't want
to make you my rebound.

341
00:22:27,100 --> 00:22:28,433
That's all.

342
00:22:29,767 --> 00:22:32,767
We don't have to rush anything.

343
00:22:32,900 --> 00:22:35,533
Let's just get to know
each other first.

344
00:22:35,667 --> 00:22:37,433
And see where it goes.

345
00:22:38,567 --> 00:22:39,767
Who knows?

346
00:22:39,900 --> 00:22:45,067
Maybe I'm the way you finally
move on from her.

347
00:22:50,833 --> 00:22:53,933
Let's just get to know
each other first.

348
00:23:08,767 --> 00:23:10,867
Could you give me some more?

349
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:12,267
Thanks.

350
00:23:12,400 --> 00:23:14,367
- Can I do it?
- Thank you.

351
00:23:20,600 --> 00:23:22,367
- Can I add more?
- Mrs. Castillo.

352
00:23:25,967 --> 00:23:31,000
You're still so hands-on,
even after the party's over.

353
00:23:31,133 --> 00:23:32,933
There are still guests outside.

354
00:23:33,067 --> 00:23:37,767
Maybe you should just let
the staff handle that?

355
00:23:37,900 --> 00:23:39,233
Oh no, it's fine.

356
00:23:39,367 --> 00:23:42,667
I can manage. I'm used to it.
This won't take long.

357
00:23:42,800 --> 00:23:45,367
It'd be such a waste
to throw these away.

358
00:23:45,500 --> 00:23:48,133
Lito can eat this tomorrow.

359
00:23:48,267 --> 00:23:49,567
Lito?

360
00:23:49,700 --> 00:23:53,767
Oh, my gosh. That's such
a cute name for a dog.

361
00:23:53,900 --> 00:23:57,467
- No...
- You know, at events like this,

362
00:23:57,633 --> 00:23:59,000
I usually just let my staff

363
00:23:59,133 --> 00:24:03,133
clear out the leftovers
and dispose of them.

364
00:24:03,267 --> 00:24:06,567
So it doesn't look embarrassing
for the guests, right?

365
00:24:07,767 --> 00:24:09,500
Oh, is that how it's done?

366
00:24:09,633 --> 00:24:14,533
I guess I'm just used
to not wasting anything.

367
00:24:14,667 --> 00:24:18,400
I figured it's better
to move the food

368
00:24:18,533 --> 00:24:20,600
than throw it in the trash.

369
00:24:20,733 --> 00:24:22,600
You do have a point.

370
00:24:22,733 --> 00:24:26,133
That's probably
where Marj gets it from.

371
00:24:26,267 --> 00:24:29,833
I raised my two boys
with class and manners

372
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:33,833
so they wouldn't pick up habits

373
00:24:33,967 --> 00:24:37,100
from uneducated,
desperate people.

374
00:24:38,467 --> 00:24:40,000
Don't worry,

375
00:24:40,133 --> 00:24:47,367
I taught my two children
to respect other people.

376
00:24:47,500 --> 00:24:50,133
Because some people,

377
00:24:50,267 --> 00:24:52,467
even if they have more
than enough money

378
00:24:52,600 --> 00:24:58,567
and more than enough food,
still somehow lack kindness.

379
00:25:04,333 --> 00:25:05,467
Mom.

380
00:25:08,133 --> 00:25:09,933
Are you okay?

381
00:25:10,067 --> 00:25:15,500
Marj, maybe you should help
your mom pack up the leftovers.

382
00:25:17,100 --> 00:25:19,833
She's not wrong.
It'd be a shame to waste it.

383
00:25:20,833 --> 00:25:22,933
Every bit counts, right?

384
00:25:23,067 --> 00:25:24,433
Even a little class.

385
00:25:31,600 --> 00:25:34,000
Oh my, I'm so sorry if
I came on a little too strong.

386
00:25:34,133 --> 00:25:36,267
But you know,

387
00:25:36,433 --> 00:25:38,400
next time there are leftovers,

388
00:25:38,533 --> 00:25:43,100
I'll tell my driver right away
to bring them to you,<i> Balae</i> .

389
00:25:44,200 --> 00:25:48,200
No, it's fine,<i> Balae</i> .

390
00:25:48,333 --> 00:25:50,000
This is enough.

391
00:25:50,133 --> 00:25:52,533
You're too kind to me.

392
00:25:52,667 --> 00:25:56,133
Oh no. Sharing is a virtue.

393
00:25:56,267 --> 00:25:58,033
Something we both value.

394
00:25:59,433 --> 00:26:01,767
Even if we go about it
differently.

395
00:26:03,233 --> 00:26:04,233
Mom.

396
00:26:04,367 --> 00:26:06,967
Mom, let's go.

397
00:26:07,100 --> 00:26:08,400
Pao and I will take you home.

398
00:26:08,567 --> 00:26:10,967
All right. That might be best.

399
00:26:11,100 --> 00:26:13,200
I might end up packing
something else.

400
00:26:14,267 --> 00:26:15,033
Okay.

401
00:26:15,167 --> 00:26:17,633
See you at the wedding,<i> Balae</i> .

402
00:26:17,767 --> 00:26:19,433
Okay.

403
00:26:19,567 --> 00:26:21,300
Bye.

404
00:26:30,867 --> 00:26:33,633
Once I become Mrs. Torrecampo,

405
00:26:33,767 --> 00:26:35,467
I'll terminate her contract

406
00:26:35,600 --> 00:26:37,600
across the entire
Torrecampo group.

407
00:26:37,733 --> 00:26:40,400
Let's rework the gown, okay?
Change the fabric.

408
00:26:40,533 --> 00:26:42,800
Change the neckline.
Let's change the bride.

409
00:26:44,700 --> 00:26:46,200
Just kidding.

410
00:26:46,333 --> 00:26:50,667
If we're exclusive now,
I'll be your plus-one here.

411
00:26:50,800 --> 00:26:52,533
You can still walk away,
you know.

412
00:26:52,667 --> 00:26:59,033
Are you sure
this is really what you want?

413
00:26:59,167 --> 00:27:02,200
Once I get in,
good luck to Marj.

414
00:27:02,333 --> 00:27:04,467
Regina, did you have
anything to do with this?

415
00:27:04,600 --> 00:27:06,167
What's happening? Where is she?
